text: @peteskomoroch @MrLarrieu It’s complex and really hard to implement in a way that serves every kid well. I don’t have all the answers but just wanted to push back on “more acceleration good, less acceleration bad.” Cause that’s just not true.

text: @peteskomoroch @MrLarrieu So you end up with these ham fisted approaches of “nobody gets to accelerate” (because equity!) or “half the kids accelerate and then fail or opt out of math in high school” (because lots of social pressure to be/have one of the smart kids).

text: @mctownsley @IADeptofEd Eehhhh sorta. In the literature there’s the idea of the written curriculum, the planned curriculum, and the enacted curriculum. So a textbook series would be the written curriculum.
